### Step 10 — Schedule recovery check

For each shipped URL, the workflow's existing observation pipeline (Task 4 — runs daily at 8 AM) will auto-monitor for first GSC pickup (~5-7 days) and 14-day rank trajectory. No separate scheduled task needed.

---

## Failure modes to handle gracefully

| Scenario | Response |
|---|---|
| Brief has malformed frontmatter | Skip + log + Slack flag |
| Reviewer pool fully loaded | Skip, retry next run |
| `npm run build` fails | Revert commits, quarantine briefs, Slack flag |
| Internal link points to non-existent page | Write MDX anyway, log warning, validate post-deploy |
| Brief mentions algo_watch HOLD | Skip silently (expected behaviour) |
| Network/git push fails | Save state, retry in next run (use git stash) |
| Brief topic is YMYL but missing `clinical_reviewer_signed_off` | Skip + log AP3 VETO + leave brief for next run (gives clinician time to sign off) |
| Brief topic is YMYL and `clinical_reviewer_signed_off.date` is stale (>90 days) | Skip + log AP3 VETO + Slack flag (clinician should re-review) |
| Brief topic is YMYL with valid sign-off | Auto-ship like a regular blog (post 2026-06-26 Option B update — AP3 satisfied via reviewer pre-approval) |

---

## Constraints (DO NOT VIOLATE)

- **Mindtalk only** in v1. Do not extend to CH/CDC/cadabams.org without explicit Kushal approval after 2-3 weeks of stable Mindtalk runs.
- **NEW blogs, NEW illness, NEW treatment.** YMYL (illness/treatment/suicide-safety) requires valid `clinical_reviewer_signed_off` (Option B, 2026-06-26). Never auto-ship REFRESH briefs of any kind.
- **5 per run, 20 per week cap.** Hard limit.
- **Brand suffix: titles MUST end with `| Mindtalk` and be ≤ 65 chars total.**
- **Reviewer required.** No anonymous blog goes live.
- **Build must succeed before push.** No exceptions.
- **One feature branch per run.** Easy revert if something looks wrong post-deploy.

## Observability — Kushal can review at any time

- `logs/auto-ship-{TODAY}.txt` — per-run log
- `logs/auto-ship-week-{WEEK-START}.txt` — weekly running tally
- `logs/briefs-{WEEK-START}.txt` — combined manual + auto-ship log (matches existing format)
- Slack `#seo-workflow-mindtalk` — every run gets a notification
- `tracking-db.json` — `auto_shipped: true` flag lets you filter/audit
- `briefs/.failed/` — quarantined briefs with error logs (debugging artefacts)

If at any time Kushal wants to pause auto-ship: open the Cowork scheduled task `mindtalk-auto-ship-new-blogs` and click "Disable". No code changes needed.

